        <article id="post-1380" class="post-1380 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-items tag-4-year-drone-degree tag-drones tag-police-state tag-the-atlantic tag-university-of-north-dakota clearfix rtp-post-box">
            
            <header class="post-header ">
                
                                            <h2 class="post-title"><a href="http://libertyblitzkrieg.com/2012/07/23/university-of-north-dakota-offers-4-year-drone-piloting-degree/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to University of North Dakota Offers 4-Year Drone-Piloting Degree">University of North Dakota Offers 4-Year Drone-Piloting Degree</a></h2>
                <?php// rtp_hook_end_post_title(); ?>

                
            <div class="clearfix post-meta post-meta-top"><span class="author"><a class="fn" href="http://libertyblitzkrieg.com/author/mkriegs/" title="Posts by Michael Krieger">Michael Krieger</a></span> <span class="rtp-meta-separator">|</span> Posted <time class="published" datetime="2012-07-23T11:21:25+00:00">Monday Jul 23, 2012</time> at 11:21 am         <span class="rtp-post-comment-count"><a href="http://libertyblitzkrieg.com/2012/07/23/university-of-north-dakota-offers-4-year-drone-piloting-degree/#respond" class="rtp-post-comment rtp-common-link"  title="Comment on University of North Dakota Offers 4-Year Drone-Piloting Degree">Leave a comment</a></span>
            </div><!-- .post-meta -->            </header><!-- .post-title -->

            <div class="post-content">
                                

                
                <p>The three P&#8217;s of America&#8217;s gulag economy at work: Ponzi schemes, Poverty and Police State.  The housing market may still be in the dumps, but the drone industry is booming.  USA! USA!</p>
<p>Key quote:<em><br />
The University of North Dakota operates a fleet of seven different types of unmanned aircraft. In 2009, it became the first college in the country to offer a four-year degree in unmanned aircraft piloting. It now has 23 graduates and 84 students majoring in the program, which is open only to U.S. citizens.</em></p>
<p>Read the article <a href="http://m.theatlantic.com/technology/archive/2012/07/university-of-north-dakota-offers-4-year-drone-piloting-degree/260156/">here</a>.</p>
